    <sec id="SEC2-4">
      <title>LocHap pipeline</title>
      <p>A computational pipeline (Figure <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F3">3</xref>) supports LocHap applications. LocHap analyzes one sample at a time and can be used sequentially or in parallel for the analysis of multiple samples. For a single sample, the input of LocHap includes (i) a <italic>bam</italic> file with the associated index <italic>bai</italic> file and (ii) a corresponding <italic>vcf</italic> file that contains the SNVs in the sample, called by any standard variant calling algorithm, such as <italic>GATK's</italic> (<xref rid="B27" ref-type="bibr">27</xref>–<xref rid="B29" ref-type="bibr">29</xref>) UnifiedGenotyper tool. The output of LocHap is a set of LHVs stored in <italic>hcf</italic> files, one for each sample.</p>
      <fig id="F3" orientation="portrait" position="float">
